description:
Fix Weak Assertions

## Problem
Tests use Assert.True/False without context messages making debugging difficult.

## Common Anti-Patterns
```csharp
// Weak assertions (current):
Assert.True(result.IsValid);
Assert.False(service.HasErrors);
Assert.Equal(expected, actual);
Assert.Throws<Exception>(() => action());
```

## Required Fix
```csharp
// Strong assertions with context:
Assert.True(result.IsValid, 
    $"Expected IsValid to be true but was false. Errors: {string.Join(", ", result.Errors)}");

Assert.False(service.HasErrors, 
    $"Expected HasErrors to be false but was true. Errors: {service.ErrorMessage}");

Assert.Equal(expected, actual, 
    $"Expected value {expected} but got {actual}");

var exception = Assert.Throws<ArgumentException>(() => action());
Assert.Contains("parameter name", exception.Message);
```

## Files to Audit
- All test files using Assert.True/False without messages
- Tests with non-specific exception types
- Missing assertion context

## Verification Steps
- Search for Assert.True without message
- Search for Assert.False without message
- Add meaningful context to all assertions
- Ensure assertions provide debugging info

