Parent: EPIC: Test Quality Improvements (Synaxis-2zrm)

Refactor God Classes

## Problem
Classes with excessive size, methods, and complexity violating SOLID principles.

## Criteria for God Class
- >500 lines of code
- >20 methods
- Cyclomatic complexity >15

## Files to Refactor
Audit and identify candidate classes:
- [ ] SynaxisDbContext (likely has multiple responsibilities)
- [ ] Service classes with >500 lines
- [ ] Controllers with business logic

## Refactoring Strategy
1. Extract Single Responsibility classes
2. Use Facade pattern for complex coordination
3. Apply Strategy pattern for varying behaviors
4. Use composition over inheritance

## Example
```csharp
// Before (God Class):
public class OrderService
{
    // 800 lines, 30 methods
    // Handles: validation, pricing, inventory, notifications, payments
}

// After (separate concerns):
public class OrderService
{
    private readonly IOrderValidator _validator;
    private readonly IPricingService _pricing;
    private readonly IInventoryService _inventory;
    private readonly INotificationService _notifications;
    private readonly IPaymentService _payments;

    public OrderService(... dependencies ...) { }
}
```

## Verification Steps
- Measure lines of code per class
- Calculate cyclomatic complexity
- Ensure unit tests still pass
- Code review approval

## Related Epic
Parent: EPIC: Code Quality Refactoring (Synaxis-72y9)

Extract Hardcoded Configuration Values

## Problem
Hardcoded values scattered throughout codebase making environment-specific deployment difficult.

## Common Patterns
- Magic strings for URLs
- Hardcoded timeouts
- Fixed retry counts
- Embedded connection strings

## Location Pattern
- Search for: "http://", timeout values, connection strings
- Configuration sections missing from appsettings

## Required Fix
```csharp
// Current (hardcoded):
public class ExternalApiService
{
    private readonly string _baseUrl = "https://api.example.com";
    private readonly int _timeout = 30;
    private readonly int _maxRetries = 3;
}

// Fixed (using Options pattern):
public class ExternalApiOptions
{
    public string BaseUrl { get; set; }
    public int TimeoutSeconds { get; set; } = 30;
    public int MaxRetries { get; set; } = 3;
}

public class ExternalApiService
{
    private readonly ExternalApiOptions _options;

    public ExternalApiService(IOptions<ExternalApiOptions> options)
    {
        _options = options.Value;
    }
}

// In Program.cs:
services.Configure<ExternalApiOptions>(
    configuration.GetSection("ExternalApi"));
```

## Configuration Categories to Extract
- [ ] External API endpoints
- [ ] Database connection strings
- [ ] Cache settings
- [ ] Rate limiting values
- [ ] Feature flags
- [ ] Logging levels

## Verification Steps
- All values in appsettings.json
- No magic strings in code
- Configuration validation on startup
- Environment-specific configs working

