Parent: EPIC: Code Quality Refactoring (Synaxis-72y9)

Fix Insecure API Key Generation - HIGH Risk

## Risk Level
HIGH - Uses non-cryptographic RNG for security tokens

## Problem
API keys are generated using Random or Guid.NewGuid() instead of cryptographically secure random number generators.

## Location
- Pattern found in: API key service implementations
- Files: Services/ApiKeyService.cs or similar

## Impact
- Predictable API keys
- Key collision vulnerabilities
- Security token bypass attacks

## Required Fix
```csharp
// Current (insecure):
public string GenerateApiKey() => Guid.NewGuid().ToString("N");

// Fixed:
public string GenerateApiKey()
{
    var bytes = new byte[32];
    using (var rng = RandomNumberGenerator.Create())
    {
        rng.GetBytes(bytes);
    }
    return Convert.ToBase64String(bytes)
        .Replace("+", "-")
        .Replace("/", "_")
        .Replace("=", "");
}
```

## Verification Steps
- Replace all Guid.NewGuid() key generation
- Use RandomNumberGenerator for tokens
- Add key entropy tests
- Verify key uniqueness in load tests

## Related Epic
Parent: EPIC: Fix Security Vulnerabilities (Synaxis-7gf0)

Fix File Upload Path Traversal Risk - MEDIUM Risk

## Risk Level
MEDIUM - Path traversal vulnerability in file uploads

## Problem
File upload endpoints do not sanitize file names, allowing directory traversal attacks.

## Location
- File upload controller endpoints
- Document upload services

## Impact
- Arbitrary file writes outside upload directory
- Overwrite of system files
- Remote code execution

## Required Fix
```csharp
// Current (vulnerable):
var filePath = Path.Combine(uploadPath, file.FileName);
await file.CopyToAsync(new FileStream(filePath, FileMode.Create));

// Fixed:
var sanitizedFileName = Path.GetFileName(file.FileName);
if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(sanitizedFileName) || 
    sanitizedFileName.Contains("..") ||
    Path.IsPathRooted(sanitizedFileName))
{
    throw new SecurityException("Invalid file name");
}

var filePath = Path.Combine(uploadPath, Guid.NewGuid() + "_" + sanitizedFileName);
var fullPath = Path.GetFullPath(filePath);
if (!fullPath.StartsWith(Path.GetFullPath(uploadPath)))
{
    throw new SecurityException("Path traversal detected");
}
await file.CopyToAsync(new FileStream(fullPath, FileMode.Create));
```

## Verification Steps
- Validate file names
- Check path traversal patterns
- Add security unit tests
- Scan with security tools

